analysis.title: Global Market Outlook
analysis.content: Volatility expansion offsets credit resilience as markets enter a phase of precarious equilibrium. The GMS 52 print confirms a neutral regime where compressing high-yield spreads conflict with a burgeoning VIX and decaying speculative sentiment. Geopolitical exogenous shocks and trade secret litigation introduce regime-degradation risks, mandating a pivot toward capital preservation until liquidity convexity re-emerges and tactical consolidation concludes. [ACTION: WAIT FOR PULLBACK]
